Genesis Energy, L.P. To Present At The Bank Of America Merrill Lynch Energy Credit Conference

        
        Genesis Energy, L.P.






Business Wire




Jun 6, 2017 6:30 AM EDT



 













































  Genesis Energy, L.P. (NYSE:GEL) announced today that Bob Deere, CFO, will speak at the Bank of America Merrill Lynch Energy Credit Conference being held June 6-7, 2017 in New York, New York. Mr. Deere will discuss Genesis Energy's performance, growth strategies and financial objectives.  The Partnership's latest presentation materials are available and may be downloaded by visiting the Partnership's website at www.genesisenergy.com under "Presentations" under the Investors tab.  Genesis Energy, L.P. is a diversified midstream energy master limited partnership headquartered in Houston, Texas. Genesis' operations include offshore pipeline transportation, refinery services, marine transportation and supply and logistics. Genesis' operations are primarily located in Texas, Louisiana, Arkansas, Mississippi, Alabama, Florida, Wyoming and the Gulf of Mexico.      View source version on businesswire.com:   http://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20170606005111/en/  



 
 
























