                                                Genesis Energy, L.P.
                                             Company Snapshot
                                            









                                            
	Genesis Energy, L.P. operates in the Petroleum bulk stations & terminals sector.
	
	In addition to historical fundamental analyses, the complete report available to purchase compares Genesis Energy, L.P. with three other
	
			companies in this sector in the United States:
		
	Crossamerica Partners LP
	
		(2016
	sales of $1.87 billion
		of which 88%
		was Wholesale),
	
	Ferrellgas Partners, L.P.
	
		($2.04 billion
		of which 69%
		was propane and realted equipment sales), and
	
	Sprague Resources LP
	
		($2.39 billion
		of which 83%
		was Refined products).
	
	Sales Analysis. 
	Genesis Energy, L.P. reported sales of $1.71 billion
		for the
		
		year ending
		December of 2016.
	
		This
		
			represents
		
			a
			
				sharp
			
			decrease of 23.8%
		
		 versus 2015, when the company's sales were $2.25 billion.
	
		Contributing to the drop in overall sales was the 38.9% decline
		in Supple and Logistics, from $1.62 billion to $993.10 million.
		
					There were also decreases in sales in
					Marine Transportation (down 10.4% to $206.21 million)
				
					and
				Refinery Services (down 3.5% to $180.67 million)
				.
		
					However, these declines were partially offset by the increase in sales of
					Offshore Pipeline Transportation (up 137.1% to $332.51 million)
				
			.
		

	




 


 
 


 
 


 
 











 



 













 










